<chapter xml:id="ch07-approximation-methods:-perturbation-theory-dimension-9-" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
  <title>Approximation Methods: Perturbation Theory (Dimension 9)</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>This chapter explores a crucial dimension of the quantum framework. Develops time-independent and time-dependent perturbation theory, provides tools for solving realistic problems, foundation for Fermi's golden rule.</p>
  </introduction>
  <section><title>Overview</title>
    <p>This chapter continues development of the 11-dimensional quantum framework. Key concepts and applications are developed systematically.</p>
  </section>
  <section><title>Core Content</title>
    <p>Detailed treatment of major topics and techniques for this domain of quantum mechanics.</p>
  </section>
  <section><title>Chapter Summary</title>
    <ul>
      <li>Key insight 1</li>
      <li>Key insight 2</li>
      <li>Key insight 3</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
